  "text": "We start with an illustration using MNIST. We compare the model architecture of [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] with two variants of our proposed DHM as shown in Figure 3 . The original architecture [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] is denoted as NDF. NDF passes some randomly chosen outputs from the last fully-connected layer to sigmoid gates, whose outputs are used as the recommendation scores s i of each dividing node. The other two structures are detailed in the following subsections.",
